          <div class="reg-header">
            <h3>Idaho's Chain Law: Three Passes Only</h3>
            <span class="reg-cite">Idaho Code 49-948</span>
          </div>
          <p>Idaho's chain law applies on <strong>three mountain passes</strong> - not statewide. National agents often don't know this.</p>
          <ul class="reg-list">
            <li><strong>Lookout Pass</strong> (I-90, Montana border)</li>
            <li><strong>Fourth of July Pass</strong> (I-90, Coeur d'Alene to Kellogg)</li>
            <li><strong>Lolo Pass</strong> (Highway 12, Montana border)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="reg-note">Agricultural, forest product, and mining haulers are EXEMPT from chain requirements.</p>
          <a href="/trucking-insurance-idaho/chain-laws/" class="reg-link">Full chain law guide &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Medical Cert -->
        <div class="reg-card highlight">
          <div class="reg-header">
            <h3>Medical Certificate Enforcement</h3>
            <span class="reg-cite">Effective April 1, 2025</span>
          </div>
          <p>Starting <strong>April 1, 2025</strong>, Idaho State Police will place drivers <strong>Out of Service (OOS)</strong> immediately if operating without a valid medical certificate on file. First offense - immediate OOS. No warnings.</p>
          <p class="reg-note"><strong>RMS recommendation:</strong> Keep a photo of your med card on your phone. When we bind your policy, we verify your medical certification status.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY RMS -->
