          <p>The primary freight corridor for Pacific Northwest produce, Port of Portland freight, Salt Lake distribution, and cross-country runs connecting I-80 and I-90.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="corridor-card">
          <h3>I-90: The Northern Crossings</h3>
          <p class="corridor-route">Lookout Pass and Fourth of July Pass</p>
          <p>Seattle/Spokane freight heading east, Coeur d'Alene and Kellogg operations, Montana and beyond. Two of Idaho's three chain law locations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="corridor-card">
          <h3>North-South Routes</h3>
          <p class="corridor-route">US-95, US-93, I-15</p>
          <p>US-95: Lewiston through Boise to Nevada (timber, ag). US-93: Twin Falls to Nevada (cattle). I-15: Eastern Idaho to Montana/Utah.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cities-section">
        <h3>Population Centers</h3>
        <div class="cities-grid">
          <div class="city"><strong>Boise</strong><span>Metro construction, distribution, HP/Micron supply chain</span></div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Twin Falls</strong><span>Chobani, Glanbia food processing, dairy transport</span></div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Pocatello</strong><span>Rail intermodal, phosphate mining</span></div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Idaho Falls</strong><span>INL contractors, agriculture, eastern corridor hub</span></div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Nampa/Caldwell</strong><span>Treasure Valley logistics, ag processing</span></div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Lewiston</strong><span>Timber, Port of Lewiston barge freight</span></div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Coeur d'Alene</strong><span>Northern Idaho hub, I-90 corridor operations</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- REQUIREMENTS -->
  <section class="requirements">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Requirements</span>
        <h2>Idaho Trucking Insurance Requirements</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table class="req-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Requirement</th>
              <th>Details</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>USDOT Number</td><td>Required for all commercial vehicles</td></tr>
            <tr><td>MC Number</td><td>Required for for-hire interstate carriers</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Minimum Liability</td><td><strong>$750,000</strong> for general freight</td></tr>
            <tr><td>BMC-91 Filing</td><td>Proof of insurance filed with FMCSA</td></tr>
            <tr><td>BOC-3 Filing</td><td>Process agent designation (required)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>UCR Registration</td><td>Annual unified carrier registration</td></tr>
            <tr><td>IFTA Registration</td><td>International Fuel Tax Agreement</td></tr>
            <tr><td>IRP Registration</td><td>International Registration Plan for apportioned plates</td></tr>
            <tr><td>HVUT</td><td>Heavy Highway Vehicle Use Tax (55,000+ lbs). File IRS Form 2290.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="req-note"><strong>Hazmat haulers:</strong> $5,000,000 minimum liability. Additional permits required.</p>
      <p class="req-note"><strong>RMS handles the federal filings.</strong> When we bind your policy, your BMC-91 files within 10 minutes. Your BOC-3 files the same day.</p>
