    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="section-tag">New Authority</span>
        <h2>New Authority in Idaho? Here's How It Works</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="day">Day 1</span>
          <p>Apply for USDOT and MC numbers ($300 FMCSA fee)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="day">Days 1-20</span>
          <p>Waiting period - FMCSA publishes but authority not active</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <span class="day">Day 18-19</span>
          <p>RMS binds your insurance and files your BMC-91</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="day">Day 21</span>
          <p>Authority goes active. You're legal to haul.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timing-note">
        <h3>Why Timing Matters</h3>
        <p>If we bind your insurance too early, you're paying for days you can't use. If we file too late, your authority doesn't activate on time. We've done this 1,000+ times - we know exactly when to pull the trigger.</p>
        <p><strong>The Idaho Advantage:</strong> As an Idaho-based company, we can meet you in person if needed. Complex situation? Questions about your authority? We're local.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
