        <div class="pricing-includes">
          <p>That includes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Auto liability ($750,000)</li>
            <li>Cargo insurance ($100,000)</li>
            <li>Physical damage (depends on truck value)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="pricing-factors">
          <h3>Factors That Affect Your Rate</h3>
          <div class="factors-grid">
            <div class="factor"><strong>Driving experience</strong><span>2+ years CDL = better rates</span></div>
            <div class="factor"><strong>MVR (driving record)</strong><span>Clean record vs. violations matters significantly</span></div>
            <div class="factor"><strong>Equipment age</strong><span>Newer trucks = higher physical damage, better liability</span></div>
            <div class="factor"><strong>Cargo type</strong><span>General freight vs. hazmat vs. specialized</span></div>
            <div class="factor"><strong>Operating radius</strong><span>Local Idaho vs. nationwide</span></div>
            <div class="factor"><strong>Weight</strong><span>105,500 lb operations vs. standard 80K</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pricing-reality">
          <p><strong>The reality for new authorities:</strong> Your carrier options are limited for the first 2 years. Progressive, Berkshire, National Indemnity - that's basically it. The rates are similar no matter which agent you use. So you're not shopping for a policy - you're shopping for an agent.</p>
          <p>That's where we come in. Same carriers, better service. 5-minute COIs. 10-minute filings. Someone who knows Idaho Code 49-948 when you ask about chains.</p>
